1269
02:02:16,220 --> 02:02:18,012
<i>Murphy tees it up behind the net...</i>

1270
02:02:22,184 --> 02:02:25,395
<i>...Miller out front.
Now here's Murphy with the referee...</i>

1271
02:02:28,983 --> 02:02:30,150
Waingro, where is he?

1272
02:02:31,527 --> 02:02:33,778
Where is he?
How the hell would I know?

1273
02:02:59,555 --> 02:03:03,475
Well, what do we have here, hmm?

1274
02:03:03,934 --> 02:03:07,562
Isn't this pretty? It's pretty. Aah!

1275
02:03:08,606 --> 02:03:09,856
(SCOFFS)

1276
02:03:10,024 --> 02:03:13,067
You slimy piece of shit.
You told me you wanted out from under.

1277
02:03:13,235 --> 02:03:16,404
You're scared to death, right?
You want out? This is out, Charlene.

1278
02:03:16,572 --> 02:03:20,241
Yeah, what's your end?
I... You stupid broad.

1279
02:03:20,409 --> 02:03:22,869
How'd I get into this?
Hey, hey, hey. Easy.

1280
02:03:23,037 --> 02:03:24,245
Huh?
You heard me.

1281
02:03:24,413 --> 02:03:27,457
She had a rough ride.
Why don't you fix her a drink or something?

1282
02:03:27,625 --> 02:03:30,627
Look in the cabinet above the sink.
Fuck her.

1283
02:03:33,047 --> 02:03:36,174
You'd better get in there and stay in there.
All right, all right.

1284
02:03:38,928 --> 02:03:41,179
Well, lookie here.

1285
02:03:42,348 --> 02:03:44,641
My name is Sergeant Drucker,
L.A.P.D. Homicide.

1286
02:03:44,808 --> 02:03:48,811
You wanna put Dominick in the bedroom?
He stays with me.

1287
02:03:49,313 --> 02:03:51,231
There we go.

1288
02:03:58,822 --> 02:04:00,782
So, what now?

1289
02:04:03,035 --> 02:04:06,788
Well, he's right,
because you want out, this is out.

1290
02:04:08,207 --> 02:04:12,085
You believe you have to betray Chris.
No shit.

1291
02:04:12,253 --> 02:04:15,213
That's right. You would have to.

1292
02:04:15,381 --> 02:04:19,634
See, if you don't betray Chris,
you victimize Dominick.

1293
02:04:20,135 --> 02:04:23,346
Because he becomes an orphan
when you go to prison as an accessory...

1294
02:04:23,514 --> 02:04:25,974
...because you got no living parents
to take him.

1295
02:04:26,141 --> 02:04:30,520
So he ends up state-raised in
foster homes, juvenile facilities.

1296
02:04:30,688 --> 02:04:32,939
Then he steals a car.

1297
02:04:33,190 --> 02:04:38,361
Then he winds up in gladiator academies
like Chino and Tracy.

1298
02:04:38,529 --> 02:04:41,823
Fucked for life.

1299
02:04:41,991 --> 02:04:45,326
You know what happens,
because you've been there.

1300
02:04:46,495 --> 02:04:51,666
Dominick didn't get a chance yet
to choose his life, but Chris did.

1301
02:04:52,751 --> 02:04:56,337
If you give up Chris, you get off clean.

1302
02:04:56,505 --> 02:05:00,425
You can do it for your kid,
so you can raise him.

1303
02:05:04,597 --> 02:05:07,974
What else are you selling?
All kinds of shit.

1304
02:05:08,851 --> 02:05:14,063
But I don't have to sell this and you know it,
because this kind of shit here sells itself.

1305
02:05:15,691 --> 02:05:17,692
(DIALING PHONE)

1306
02:05:20,362 --> 02:05:22,363
<i>DRUCKER (OVER PHONE):
Okay, Danny, here's an update.</i>

1307
02:05:22,531 --> 02:05:25,867
Drucker's on Line 2.
Lieutenant, hold on for a second.

1308
02:05:28,037 --> 02:05:30,163
Lieutenant, I have Drucker
on the other line.

1309
02:05:30,331 --> 02:05:31,706
Oh, well, conference him in.

1310
02:05:33,208 --> 02:05:36,919
Go ahead.
Vincent, it's me.

1311
02:05:38,839 --> 02:05:41,466
I want an answer. What's it gonna be?

1312
02:05:48,057 --> 02:05:50,558
We're set here. She'll make the call.

1313
02:05:50,726 --> 02:05:53,895
Okay, that's good. Here's the deal here.

1314
02:05:54,063 --> 02:05:59,901
Hugh Benny has reformed his wayward life
and become a born-again good citizen.

1315
02:06:00,069 --> 02:06:04,614
Apparently, Neil got sold out to us
by this cowboy named Waingro.

1316
02:06:04,782 --> 02:06:07,533
Waingro used to be a part
of Neil's crew...

1317
02:06:07,701 --> 02:06:11,287
...then he went to work
for a money launderer named Van Zant.

1318
02:06:11,455 --> 02:06:17,251
Units are at Van Zant's house as we speak
because he got shot dead earlier tonight.

1319
02:06:17,586 --> 02:06:20,922
Now, if Neil goes after anybody else,
it's gonna be Waingro.

1320
02:06:21,090 --> 02:06:24,425
Waingro just got himself a suite
at the airport Marquis...

1321
02:06:24,593 --> 02:06:27,970
...under the name "Jameson."
He's there now.

1322
02:06:28,138 --> 02:06:31,224
I want you to get that
to bail bondsmen, bookies...

1323
02:06:31,392 --> 02:06:34,602
<i>...assignment officers
and snitches in County.</i>

1324
02:06:34,770 --> 02:06:37,146
Anyone you can think of
who'll put it on the street.

1325
02:06:37,314 --> 02:06:41,484
Deploy a team at the hotel and personally
check their coms every 30 minutes.

1326
02:06:41,652 --> 02:06:45,738
Because maybe Neil will go for him.
Okay? How you feeling?

1327
02:06:46,448 --> 02:06:49,701
Banged up, but I'll live.
Okay.

1328
02:06:57,084 --> 02:06:58,960
He's here.

1329
02:06:59,253 --> 02:07:01,462
Neil is still here.

1330
02:07:02,005 --> 02:07:03,965
I can feel it.

1331
02:07:04,216 --> 02:07:06,759
But for how long?
Uh...

1332
02:07:07,344 --> 02:07:10,263
Seven, eight hours, max.

1333
02:07:18,647 --> 02:07:19,981
EADY: What did you do?

1334
02:07:20,691 --> 02:07:24,402
That was you?
It's what I don't do, I don't sell metal.

1335
02:07:24,570 --> 02:07:27,488
Would have been okay, you fly out after.
Now it's jammed.

1336
02:07:27,656 --> 02:07:31,659
Now we gotta go together.
Those other people were with you?

1337
02:07:33,787 --> 02:07:35,913
My friend, Michael...

1338
02:07:36,999 --> 02:07:39,625
...he knew the risks.
He didn't have to be there.

1339
02:07:43,630 --> 02:07:46,257
It rains, you get wet.

1340
02:07:48,302 --> 02:07:49,510
Get packed and let's go.

1341
02:07:56,685 --> 02:07:57,852
Eady.

1342
02:07:58,312 --> 02:07:59,353
Eady.

1343
02:08:09,114 --> 02:08:12,366
EADY: Why did you do this to me?

1344
02:08:17,873 --> 02:08:19,916
Who are you?

1345
02:08:22,753 --> 02:08:25,880
NEIL: It's gonna be all right.
You understand? It'll be all right.

1346
02:08:26,381 --> 02:08:28,132
(GROANS)

1347
02:08:30,761 --> 02:08:32,887
It's gonna be all right.

1348
02:08:33,889 --> 02:08:35,515
Right.

1349
02:08:44,107 --> 02:08:47,735
There's this Camaro at this address,
Level D, Slot 18.

1350
02:08:52,449 --> 02:08:54,492
Here's some cash.

1351
02:08:57,079 --> 02:08:58,246
When's it over?

1352
02:09:01,750 --> 02:09:03,292
Twenty-two hours from now.

1353
02:09:03,752 --> 02:09:07,463
Then we get out of here clean.
When will you let me leave?

1354
02:09:11,385 --> 02:09:14,262
Go now. You want out? There's the door.

1355
02:09:14,930 --> 02:09:17,098
Will you let me leave later?

1356
02:09:22,187 --> 02:09:24,397
It will be different.

1357
02:09:25,440 --> 02:09:27,608
Do you understand?

1358
02:09:58,098 --> 02:09:59,640
It's ready.

1359
02:09:59,808 --> 02:10:01,642
Vincent.

1360
02:10:07,065 --> 02:10:09,233
This is my friend Ralph.

1361
02:10:09,401 --> 02:10:11,360
RALPH:
You didn't tell me you were...

1362
02:10:12,446 --> 02:10:15,323
Oh, my God.
Where's Lauren?

1363
02:10:15,490 --> 02:10:18,701
She's at Lisa-Beth's.
Look, this has nothing to do with me.

1364
02:10:18,869 --> 02:10:22,788
I didn't know. I'm terribly sorry.
What are you sorry about? Sit down.

1365
02:10:23,457 --> 02:10:25,499
JUSTINE: Don't you even get angry?

1366
02:10:25,667 --> 02:10:28,169
I'm angry, yeah.
Oh.

1367
02:10:28,337 --> 02:10:30,755
I'm very angry, Ralph.

1368
02:10:30,923 --> 02:10:34,008
You know, you can ball my wife
if she wants you to.

1369
02:10:35,594 --> 02:10:38,679
You can lounge around here on her sofa.

1370
02:10:40,015 --> 02:10:42,308
In her ex-husband's...

1371
02:10:42,476 --> 02:10:47,521
...dead-tech, post-modernistic,
bullshit house, if you want to...

1372
02:10:49,358 --> 02:10:55,696
...but you do not get to watch
my fucking television set!

1373
02:10:55,864 --> 02:10:57,365
JUSTINE: For God's sake.

1374
02:11:03,914 --> 02:11:05,706
Put the television set down.

1375
02:11:05,874 --> 02:11:08,417
I never cheated on you, bitch.
Maybe you should have.

1376
02:11:08,585 --> 02:11:10,878
I should have?
In a way, you're a party to this.

1377
02:11:11,046 --> 02:11:14,090
Oh, yeah. I made Ralph fuck you
because it makes me feel good.

1378
02:11:14,257 --> 02:11:15,424
Our situation is absurd.

1379
02:11:17,135 --> 02:11:21,973
Look, maybe I should...
Shut up, Ralph. Sit down!

1380
02:11:24,059 --> 02:11:27,979
Why is it that I have to figure things out
and explain them to you? What do you do?

1381
02:11:28,146 --> 02:11:31,983
I say what I mean, and I do what I say.
Mm, how admirable.

1382
02:11:32,150 --> 02:11:34,235
You bet.
Except none of it's about us.

1383
02:11:35,070 --> 02:11:36,112
No.

1384
02:11:37,572 --> 02:11:41,158
I may be stoned on grass and Prozac...

1385
02:11:41,326 --> 02:11:43,953
