through our life dead.

1386
02:11:44,121 --> 02:11:48,791
Now I have to demean myself with Ralph
just to get closure with you.

1387
02:12:01,346 --> 02:12:03,597
Passports, traveler's checks, plastic.

1388
02:12:04,266 --> 02:12:09,103
The plane, charter terminal, LAX,
Hangar 17.

1389
02:12:09,271 --> 02:12:11,022
Call letters are 1011 Sierra.

1390
02:12:11,231 --> 02:12:12,815
(TIRES SCREECH)

1391
02:12:14,401 --> 02:12:18,112
Touches down, holds for you five minutes,
then splits.

1392
02:12:18,280 --> 02:12:21,782
The plane will stand an FAA check.
Filed a flight plan, the works.

1393
02:12:23,785 --> 02:12:26,120
Hey, where's Chris?
He's gone.

1394
02:12:27,581 --> 02:12:28,622
What?

1395
02:12:29,249 --> 02:12:31,792
Said he's going on his own.
Went to look for Charlene.

1396
02:12:31,960 --> 02:12:34,795
Didn't you bring him here?
Yeah, I brought him here.

1397
02:12:35,255 --> 02:12:37,089
What happened?

1398
02:12:37,257 --> 02:12:39,633
It's a free country, brother.

1399
02:12:44,056 --> 02:12:48,476
Check in with me at 9.
Everything's still cool.

1400
02:12:49,811 --> 02:12:51,479
All right.

1401
02:13:14,044 --> 02:13:17,004
I don't even know
what I'm doing anymore.

1402
02:13:19,883 --> 02:13:22,093
I know life is short.

1403
02:13:22,344 --> 02:13:24,970
Whatever time you get is luck.

1404
02:13:27,182 --> 02:13:29,266
You wanna walk?

1405
02:13:31,520 --> 02:13:33,813
You walk right now.

1406
02:13:34,898 --> 02:13:37,024
Or on your own...

1407
02:13:37,192 --> 02:13:40,236
On your own,
you choose to come with me.

1408
02:13:46,326 --> 02:13:48,369
All I know is...

1409
02:13:50,163 --> 02:13:54,500
All I know is there's no point in me
going anywhere anymore...

1410
02:13:55,043 --> 02:13:57,128
...if it's gonna be alone...

1411
02:13:58,046 --> 02:13:59,839
...without you.

1412
02:14:06,680 --> 02:14:08,264
Eady.

1413
02:14:55,145 --> 02:14:57,188
(PHONE BEEPS)

1414
02:14:57,981 --> 02:15:00,441
Yeah.
Yeah, Vincent, I got a live one.

1415
02:15:01,151 --> 02:15:02,776
Okay, I'll hold.

1416
02:15:05,447 --> 02:15:06,822
Come on, sugar. Show yourself.

1417
02:15:07,949 --> 02:15:09,783
Yeah, do it.
Shut up!

1418
02:15:14,039 --> 02:15:16,749
Now, just one second at the window...

1419
02:15:17,542 --> 02:15:19,293
...and it's all over.

1420
02:15:49,157 --> 02:15:51,158
(CHATTERING IN DISTANCE)

1421
02:17:09,279 --> 02:17:10,946
CHRIS: Hey, man.

1422
02:17:11,197 --> 02:17:13,157
Yeah?
You know any, uh...

1423
02:17:13,325 --> 02:17:16,118
...place to rent around here?

1424
02:17:17,203 --> 02:17:18,329
MAN: Yeah.

1425
02:17:18,496 --> 02:17:21,081
Alberiz's Grocer on Dell Avenue
got cards on the wall.

1426
02:17:21,249 --> 02:17:22,291
CHRIS: Yeah, thanks.

1427
02:17:33,511 --> 02:17:36,180
It's not him. It's not Chris.

1428
02:17:43,855 --> 02:17:45,981
Unit 2, this is Command.

1429
02:17:46,149 --> 02:17:48,817
Take him at the street and check him out.

1430
02:17:48,985 --> 02:17:50,486
<i>OFFICER (OVER RADIO): 10-4.</i>

1431
02:17:59,037 --> 02:18:00,537
(TIRES SCREECH)

1432
02:18:13,927 --> 02:18:15,886
OFFICER (OVER RADIO): Sergeant?
Yeah.

1433
02:18:16,054 --> 02:18:18,639
This guy's John Peterson. Valid ID.

1434
02:18:18,807 --> 02:18:22,559
<i>Car's registered to the last
name Bukowski, first name Gene.</i>

1435
02:18:22,727 --> 02:18:25,604
<i>Ran it to DMV. It's clean.</i>

1436
02:18:28,316 --> 02:18:31,151
Let him go.
Roger.

1437
02:18:31,319 --> 02:18:33,654
Thank you very much.
Have a good evening.

1438
02:18:35,407 --> 02:18:37,366
It's a no-go, Vince.

1439
02:18:46,459 --> 02:18:49,253
Would you like a cup of coffee
while we wait, Mrs. Shiherlis?

1440
02:18:49,421 --> 02:18:51,505
Yeah, that'd be nice.

1441
02:19:21,494 --> 02:19:23,495
MAN (OVER PHONE): Yeah?
Yeah, what do you got?

1442
02:19:23,663 --> 02:19:25,747
<i>MAN: Nothing's happening.</i>

1443
02:19:33,965 --> 02:19:36,258
(PHONE RINGS)

1444
02:19:37,051 --> 02:19:40,387
Yeah?
Hello, it's Vincent.

1445
02:19:40,555 --> 02:19:41,555
<i>What do you got?</i>

1446
02:19:41,723 --> 02:19:46,059
Nothing's going on. Waingro went for ice.
That's it.

1447
02:19:54,402 --> 02:19:56,236
You know what?

1448
02:19:58,239 --> 02:20:00,282
Neil is gone.

1449
02:20:02,494 --> 02:20:04,119
Bam!

1450
02:20:04,704 --> 02:20:08,123
Flying like a bird.
Come on, Vincent, how do you know?

1451
02:20:10,418 --> 02:20:13,462
We still got bait. Maybe some time!
Got, got. What do we got?

1452
02:20:13,630 --> 02:20:15,464
What do we got?

1453
02:20:15,882 --> 02:20:18,550
Bon voyage, motherfucker.

1454
02:20:19,260 --> 02:20:21,470
You were good.

1455
02:20:22,555 --> 02:20:24,097
I'm going to the hotel.

1456
02:20:25,517 --> 02:20:27,976
I'm gonna take a shower.

1457
02:20:28,561 --> 02:20:32,064
Gonna sleep for a month.

1458
02:20:39,864 --> 02:20:41,865
(ENGINE TURNING OVER)

1459
02:20:42,700 --> 02:20:44,701
(ENGINE STARTS)

1460
02:22:41,986 --> 02:22:43,779
Over here.

1461
02:22:50,453 --> 02:22:52,371
Come on, baby.

1462
02:22:54,332 --> 02:22:56,625
Okay, okay.

1463
02:23:00,088 --> 02:23:02,047
Shit.

1464
02:23:02,924 --> 02:23:04,925
Let me tighten this.

1465
02:23:10,431 --> 02:23:12,432
What a fucking waste.

1466
02:23:12,600 --> 02:23:14,935
Okay, here.

1467
02:23:15,770 --> 02:23:21,483
Assholes shoot themselves all fucking day.
Not you, baby. Not you.

1468
02:23:26,322 --> 02:23:29,783
(STAMMERS) Where would she be?
Her name is Lauren, Lauren Gustafson.

1469
02:23:29,951 --> 02:23:32,202
I'm supposed to be here with her.
But the police...

1470
02:23:39,127 --> 02:23:42,295
Help me. I need somebody to help...
It's okay.

1471
02:23:43,756 --> 02:23:45,340
I got you.

1472
02:23:47,969 --> 02:23:49,136
I got you, baby.

1473
02:23:50,471 --> 02:23:53,807
It'll be all right, honey. I swear.
It's okay, baby.

1474
02:23:53,975 --> 02:23:58,019
Let's get a doctor! Let's go!
A doctor here! There's your mama.

1475
02:23:58,187 --> 02:24:00,063
Let's just calm down.
Your mama's here.

1476
02:24:00,231 --> 02:24:02,065
Is she on any drugs?
No.

1477
02:24:04,986 --> 02:24:07,779
I want you to get a trauma surgeon
and a vascular surgeon.

1478
02:24:07,947 --> 02:24:11,199
I think she cut both arteries.
Also, I could hardly feel her pulse.

1479
02:24:11,367 --> 02:24:14,703
Her pressure's down. So is her respiration.
You have to intubate her.

1480
02:24:14,871 --> 02:24:16,580
NURSE: It's ready.
Oh...

1481
02:24:18,082 --> 02:24:21,251
When's the last time anybody saw her?
I don't know.

1482
02:24:21,419 --> 02:24:24,504
Where did you find her?
The bathtub.

1483
02:24:24,672 --> 02:24:28,216
Call Respiratory stat. Give her large-bore
normal saline. Wide open.

1484
02:24:28,384 --> 02:24:31,511
Let's keep pressure on those bleeders.
I need two units, O-negative.

1485
02:24:31,679 --> 02:24:34,723
Let's type and cross her for six.
NURSE: Looks like she's in sinus tach.

1486
02:24:34,891 --> 02:24:36,767
DOCTOR:
Where is Respiratory? We need more help.

1487
02:24:36,934 --> 02:24:38,727
Can you have Respiratory come now?

1488
02:24:38,895 --> 02:24:41,605
Let's have X-ray ready
for post-intubation chest x-ray.

1489
02:24:46,611 --> 02:24:51,239
Hi. Your daughter's out of surgery
and she's in the recovery room now, okay?

1490
02:24:51,407 --> 02:24:55,577
Her vital signs are stable. The surgeon will
be out to speak to you in a few moments.

1491
02:24:55,745 --> 02:24:57,621
She's okay?
She's doing good.

1492
02:24:57,789 --> 02:24:59,956
She's gonna be okay.
VINCENT: She's gonna be okay.

1493
02:25:00,124 --> 02:25:03,001
(SOBBING) Oh, my baby.
She's gonna be okay. It's all right.

1494
02:25:03,169 --> 02:25:06,296
It's all right.
Why'd she do this to herself? Why?

1495
02:25:06,464 --> 02:25:10,675
Look what she did.
Look what she did to herself.

1496
02:25:11,719 --> 02:25:13,553
There.

1497
02:25:13,971 --> 02:25:16,890
It's all right, honey.
It's gonna be all right.

1498
02:25:17,058 --> 02:25:19,100
I'm here. I ain't going anywhere.

1499
02:25:19,268 --> 02:25:20,310
You understand?
Yeah.

1500
02:25:20,478 --> 02:25:22,562
I ain't going anywhere.

1501
02:25:27,527 --> 02:25:29,653
(DIALING PHONE)

1502
02:25:34,200 --> 02:25:35,200
(PHONE RINGS)

1503
02:25:35,368 --> 02:25:36,201
Yeah?

1504
02:25:36,869 --> 02:25:37,869
It's me.

1505
02:25:38,454 --> 02:25:41,706
Plane's in the air now.
It'll be right on time.

1506
02:25:41,916 --> 02:25:45,919
On the driver's end, I still can't
find nobody, so that's in the trust.

1507
02:25:46,087 --> 02:25:47,963
<i>One other thing.</i>

1508
02:25:48,422 --> 02:25:50,006
<i>You asked, so I gotta tell you.</i>

1509
02:25:50,842 --> 02:25:53,718
The guy you wanted checked into
the Marquis under "Jameson"...

1510
02:25:53,886 --> 02:25:57,264
...if you still give a shit,
which I figured you wouldn't.

1511
02:25:57,431 --> 02:26:01,184
You figured right.
So, so long, brother.

1512
02:26:02,895 --> 02:26:04,855
You take it easy.

1513
02:26:05,022 --> 02:26:06,606
You're home free.

1514
02:26:08,359 --> 02:26:10,318
Take it easy.

1515
02:26:20,663 --> 02:26:23,415
What is it?
Nothing.

1516
02:26:23,583 --> 02:26:25,125
Home free.

1517
02:27:03,080 --> 02:27:05,999
I gotta take care of something.
Is there time?

1518
02:27:07,001 --> 02:27:08,668
There's time.

1519
02:27:37,073 --> 02:27:40,200
I'll be right back.
Just leave her running.

1520
02:28:04,767 --> 02:28:06,768
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1521
02:28:21,617 --> 02:28:24,077
WOMAN (OVER PHONE): Registration.
Yeah, this is Room Service.

1522
02:28:24,245 --> 02:28:28,081
A Jameson ordered a BLT. They screwed up
his room number. Could you give it to me?

1523
02:28:28,249 --> 02:28:30,125
<i>They're always doing that.
Yeah, I know.</i>

1524
02:28:30,292 --> 02:28:33,378
<i>1735.
Thank you.</i>

1525
02:30:15,439 --> 02:30:16,689
(ALARM RINGING)

1526
02:30:16,857 --> 02:30:18,566
<i>WOMAN (ON INTERCOM):
Your attention, please.</i>

1527
02:30:18,734 --> 02:30:21,986
<i>We are currently experiencing
a fire alarm.</i>

1528
02:30:22,154 --> 02:30:25,532
<i>Please do not panic.
Please do not take the elevators.</i>

1529
02:30:29,537 --> 02:30:32,163
MAN: Shit.
Waingro's not moving. I'm staying here.

1530
02:30:32,331 --> 02:30:35,917
I'm checking the stairs.
If there's smoke, I'm pulling you out.

1531
02:30:40,214 --> 02:30:42,632
What about her dad?
You want me to call him?

1532
02:30:43,634 --> 02:30:46,469
He's somewhere in the Sierras.

1533
02:30:47,930 --> 02:30:50,098
And she chose you.

1534
02:30:52,101 --> 02:30:54,477
She picked your place.

1535
02:30:56,021 --> 02:30:57,480
It's not right, what happened to her.

1536
02:30:57,648 --> 02:30:58,982
(PAGER BEEPING)

1537
02:30:59,150 --> 02:31:00,483
No, it's not.

1538
02:31:03,904 --> 02:31:05,947
Ugh, okay.

1539
02:31:16,125 --> 02:31:18,251
Is there any way...

1540
02:31:20,212 --> 02:31:22,714
...that it could work out between us?

1541
02:31:25,092 --> 02:31:27,677
I wish I could say yes, you know.

1542
02:31:27,845 --> 02:31:31,139
But in the end...

1543
02:31:35,603 --> 02:31:37,770
You know, it's like you said:

1544
02:31:40,482 --> 02:31:45,153
All I am, is what I'm going after.

1545
02:31:52,036 --> 02:31:54,954
I'm not what you want, Justine.

1546
02:32:05,424 --> 02:32:08,051
Well, go on, if you have to.

1547
02:32:08,219 --> 02:32:09,802
No.

1548
02:32:10,095 --> 02:32:13,306
I'll stay.
No, I'm okay. I can... I can handle this.

1549
02:32:15,267 --> 02:32:16,309
(SIGHS)

1550
02:32:16,477 --> 02:32:18,478
Just be careful.

1551
02:32:18,729 --> 02:32:21,481
Call me here. Let me know you're okay.

1552
02:32:22,399 --> 02:32:23,942
Okay?

1553
02:32:54,682 --> 02:32:56,557
(ALARM RINGING)

1554
02:33:05,818 --> 02:33:06,859
MAN: Take the stairs.

1555
02:33:20,833 --> 02:33:21,874
Yeah?

1556
02:33:24,086 --> 02:33:28,256
Security. There's a fire on 3.
We have to evacuate all the floors.

1557
02:33:28,424 --> 02:33:30,049
I can't leave here.

1558
02:33:38,934 --> 02:33:42,353
Why don't we just talk about this a bit,
huh, brother?

1559
02:33:53,157 --> 02:33:55,116
(GRUNTING)

1560
02:33:56,368 --> 02:33:57,410
He's here on 17.

1561
02:34:00,581 --> 02:34:02,915
Look at me. Look at me.

1562
02:34:06,253 --> 02:34:07,420
Look at me.

1563
02:34:14,094 --> 02:34:15,470
(GASPS)

1564
02:34:20,267 --> 02:34:21,893
(SIREN WAILING)

1565
02:34:39,328 --> 02:34:43,206
L.A.P.D. Don't move.
Put your hands on your head, now.

1566
02:34:48,212 --> 02:34:50,129
(GRUNTING)

1567
02:35:18,325 --> 02:35:20,660
VINCENT: Switch me to TAC 5.

1568
02:35:20,828 --> 02:35:23,162
Casals? JJ?

1569
02:35:24,081 --> 02:35:25,289
Drucker, JJ?

1570
02:35:25,457 --> 02:35:28,000
<i>CASALS (OVER RADIO):
I'm at the lobby level by the stairwell.</i>

1571
02:35:28,168 --> 02:35:29,168
What have you got?

1572
02:35:29,336 --> 02:35:32,505
<i>CASALS: Teams are moving up the other
elevators to the 17th floor elevators.</i>

1573
02:35:32,673 --> 02:35:34,841
<i>All out of commission
because of the fire alarm.</i>

1574
02:35:35,008 --> 02:35:38,136
<i>It's a mess. People everywhere.
Fine. 10-4.</i>

1575
02:36:07,958 --> 02:36:09,542
OFFICER 1:
Let's go, get out of the way.

1576
02:36:09,710 --> 02:36:11,627
Stay out of the way.

1577
02:36:19,553 --> 02:36:22,597
Let's go. Go that way.
We gotta go, all right? Go, go.

1578
02:36:25,726 --> 02:36:27,643
OFFICER 2: I got it, sir.

1579
02:36:29,771 --> 02:36:31,689
Come on, come on.

1580
02:36:37,529 --> 02:36:39,155
Come on, sir.

1581
02:36:43,410 --> 02:36:46,412
OFFICER 1: Watch your backs, ladies.
OFFICER 2: I got it, I got it.

1582
02:36:49,082 --> 02:36:50,750
OFFICER 3: Keep moving, ma'am.

1583
02:36:51,585 --> 02:36:52,668
OFFICER 4: Let's go.

1584
02:36:55,172 --> 02:36:56,422
OFFICER 1: Come on, let's go.

1585
02:37:31,041 --> 02:37:32,708
OFFICER 2: This way, ma'am.

1586
02:37:34,670 --> 02:37:36,462
Get back, get back.

1587
02:38:02,322 --> 02:38:04,740
Let me have that shotgun.
Yes, sir.

1588
02:40:12,744 --> 02:40:13,786
(GUN CLICKS)

1589
02:44:22,202 --> 02:44:24,954
Told you I'm never going back.

1590
02:44:28,291 --> 02:44:29,917
Yeah.

